Skin care is no joke, i’ve realized that more recently. Getting treatments to prevent damage, and heel what has already been done, is so important! Microneeding is one of those treatments that do both. 

Microneedling involves using a device with fine needles to create tiny, controlled injuries on the skin’s surface. This triggers the body’s wound healing response, which involves the production of collagen and elastin.

As the skin heals, the new collagen and elastin fibers improve skin texture, reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, and can help with other skin concerns.

I was excited to share about this because i feel like it’s not talked about a ton, and it should be. 
i’ve always had a nose tick since i was little, and more recently i’ve developed ones that make me blink hard and raise my eyebrows. (probably stems from not wearing my glasses as much as i should 🤦🏼‍♀️) but it got to a point where it was affecting me daily. @elamarskin was so amazing at explaining every little detail i needed to hear. i have only ever had facials before this, so i was a little hesitant. i never thought botox could help something like this, but i’ve already felt a difference. and yes, it’s a cosmetic plus side too 💃🏼 

if you’re unsure about a treatment, starting off with a consultation is THE BEST. being able to talk through my needs with @elamarskin before any treatment is so reassuring.
